'''Neko-naki Onsen''' (猫啼温泉) is a {{ill|Hot Spring|de|Thermalquelle|ja|温泉|1=Onsen|1=Onsen|12=draft}} located in {{ill|Fukushima Prefecture|de|Fukushima-Präfektur|ja|福島県|12=draft}}, {{ill|Ishikawa District|de|Ishikawa-Kreis|ja|石川郡|12=draft}}, {{ill|Ishikawa Town|de|Ishikawa-Stadt|ja|石川町|12=draft}} (formerly part of the old {{ill|Ritsuryō State|de|Ritsuryō‑Staat|ja|令制国|lt=State|lt_ja=国|lt_de=State|12=draft}} {{ill|Mutsu Province|de|Mutsu‑Provinz|ja|陸奥国|12=draft}}; and since the {{ill|Meiji|de|Meiji|ja|明治|1=Meiji era|12=draft}} era, part of the old {{ill|Iwaki Province|de|Iwaki‑Provinz|ja|磐城国|12=draft}}).

== Water Quality ==
* Simple weak radioactive cold mineral spring
** {{ill|Spring Source|de|Quell|ja|源泉|1=Spring Mouth|12=draft}}{{ill|Temperature|de|Temperatur|ja|温度|12=draft}}8.0°C

== Hot Spring Area ==
Although there is no {{ill|Hot Spring Town|de|Onsen‑Stadt|ja|温泉街|12=draft}}, there are two {{ill|Inn|de|Gasthaus|ja|旅館|12=draft}}s located in the basin of {{ill|Imadegawa (Fukushima)|de|Imadegawa (Fukushima)|ja|今出川 (福島県)|lt=Imadegawa|lt_ja=今出川|lt_de=Imadegawa|12=draft}}.

Novels set in the local inns have also been written, such as {{ill|Yasuo Uchida|de|Yasuo Uchida|ja|内田康夫|12=draft}}’s “Thirteen Tombstones” and {{ill|Seiichi Funahashi|de|Seiichi Funahashi|ja|舟橋聖一|12=draft}}’s “A Certain Woman’s Distant View”.

== History ==
This hot spring is said to be associated with the mid‑Heian period female {{ill|Poet|de|Dichter|ja|歌人|12=draft}}, {{ill|Izumi Shikibu|de|Izumi Shikibu|ja|和泉式部|12=draft}}. According to the {{ill|Legend of the Spring’s Opening|de|Legende der Quelle|ja|開湯伝説|1=Onsen Origin Myth|12=draft}}, when Izumi Shikibu was en route to Kyoto, she left her {{ill|Cat|de|Katze|ja|ネコ|lt=Beloved Cat|lt_ja=愛猫|lt_de=Geliebte Katze|12=draft}} behind. It is said that the abandoned cat continued to cry in search of its master, Izumi Shikibu. Consequently, the hot spring came to be known as Neko‑naki Onsen. Later, although the cat fell ill, it regained its vitality after soaking in the hot spring. This discovery of the mineral spring’s healing properties by the locals led to the development of the area as a spa resort.

== Access ==
* By car: approximately 20 minutes via {{ill|Abukuma Kogen Road|de|Abukuma‑Hochlandstraße|ja|あぶくま高原道路|12=draft}} and {{ill|Tamagawa Interchange (Fukushima)|de|Tamagawa Anschlussstelle (Fukushima)|ja|玉川インターチェンジ (福島県)|lt=Tamagawa IC|lt_ja=玉川IC|lt_de=Tamagawa IC|12=draft}} from {{ill|National Route 118|de|Nationalstraße 118|ja|国道118号|12=draft}}, and approximately 40 minutes via {{ill|Tohoku Expressway|de|Tohoku‑Autobahn|ja|東北自動車道|12=draft}} and {{ill|Sukagawa Interchange|de|Sukagawa Anschlussstelle|ja|須賀川インターチェンジ|lt=Sukagawa IC|lt_ja=須賀川IC|lt_de=Sukagawa IC|12=draft}} from {{ill|National Route 118|de|Nationalstraße 118|ja|国道118号|12=draft}}.
* By train: approximately a 15‑minute walk from {{ill|Mizugun Line|de|Mizugun‑Linie|ja|水郡線|12=draft}} {{ill|Ishikawa Station|de|Ishikawa Bahnhof|ja|磐城石川駅|12=draft}}.

